    "description": "Comment ‘OSINT’ to get the deep dive. Iran shut down the Strait of Hormuz. Ship traffic dropped nearly 100%. Then they opened a toll booth — $3M per ship to pass through.\nI built a God’s Eye View to track every vessel, every dark transit, and every strike in real time. Satellite data, ship tracking, pipeline routes, dark vessel detection — all on a 3D globe. What I found is worse than what’s being reported.\nA fifth of the world’s oil supply flows through this 21-mile chokepoint. Ships are going dark mid-transit to get IRGC escort. Countries are burning through their reserves. Pakistan has 10 days left. India has 22. And the strikes on both sides keep escalating.\nThis is the god’s eye view you won’t see anywhere else. \n\n#StraitOfHormuz #Iran #OSINT #SpatialIntelligence #GodsEyeView",
